Case Study: Identity Theft – Online Loan Fraud

Cybercrime (Identity Theft) is when someone illegally uses another person’s personal information like ID details, bank data, or passwords for fraud. It is a serious online crime that can lead to financial loss and misuse of identity.
A real-life case was reported in India, where an engineer became a victim of identity theft. Hackers used his personal details such as Aadhaar and PAN card information to take multiple loans and perform online transactions without his knowledge.

  This is how it happened:
The victim’s personal details were accessed by unknown hackers through online sources.
The hackers used his identity documents to apply for loans.
Multiple loans were approved without the victim’s awareness.
The fraud was discovered only when he received notices to repay loans he never took.

Target group:
People who share personal information online
Individuals who do not secure their digital accounts properly

Consequences:
Financial loss and debt burden
Misuse of personal identity
Mental stress and confusion for the victim

Conclusion:
This case highlights how dangerous cybercrime like identity theft can be. It shows the importance of protecting personal information and being careful while using digital platforms.
